        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Check ClawHub trust before plugin and skill installs",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nOpenClaw install/update flows now enforce ClawHub trust for community plugin and skill releases, while treating official OpenClaw sources as trusted first-party installs. Malicious or ClawHub-blocked community releases fail before download; suspicious community releases require explicit acknowledgement; official ClawHub and bundled OpenClaw installs bypass the trust/security/policy friction entirely.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nClawHub now marks official publishers/packages, and bundled OpenClaw plugins/skills are already first-party code shipped with the product. Warning or blocking those sources on the same path as unknown community code creates false friction and can block official installs when ClawHub scan state changes.\n\n## User Impact\n\n| Case | Behavior |\n| --- | --- |\n| Community malicious plugin/skill install | Blocks before download; installed item is unchanged. |\n| Community suspicious plugin/skill install | Requires interactive acknowledgement or `--acknowledge-clawhub-risk`. |\n| Community malicious/suspicious update | Does not download the latest release unless the risk is explicitly acknowledged where allowed. |\n| Official ClawHub plugin install | Skips ClawHub trust/security friction and install-policy hooks; normal compatibility checks still apply. |\n| Official ClawHub skill install | Skips trust/security friction when ClawHub returns structured official metadata on the skill, owner, install resolution, or archive. |\n| Bundled OpenClaw plugin install | Installs without ClawHub trust warnings or install-policy friction. |\n| Bundled OpenClaw skill surface | Loads as `openclaw-bundled` without ClawHub trust warnings; bundled skill install-policy paths bypass operator friction. |\n\n## Evidence\n\nPR head: `529f0a578b24b5a0ec09194df1ada67713c5a12b` (`529f0a578b24`).\n\n### Live ClawHub / Local CLI Checks\n\n| Surface | Command / source | Result |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| Official ClawHub plugin metadata | `GET /api/v1/packages/%40openclaw%2Fmatrix` | `channel: \"official\"`, `isOfficial: true`, `scanStatus: \"suspicious\"`. |\n| Official ClawHub plugin install | `node dist/entry.js plugins install clawhub:@openclaw/matrix --force` | No ClawHub trust warning/block; stops on normal compatibility because this PR branch is still OpenClaw `2026.6.8` while live Matrix requires plugin API `>=2026.6.10`. |\n| Official ClawHub plugin install | `node dist/entry.js plugins install clawhub:@openclaw/kitchen-sink --force` | No ClawHub trust warning/block; stops on normal compatibility because live Kitchen Sink requires OpenClaw `>=2026.6.9`. |\n| Bundled plugin install | `node dist/entry.js plugins install acpx --force` | Exit `0`; output is only bundled-source notice, success, and restart hint. No ClawHub trust warning. |\n| Peter skill install | `node dist/entry.js skills install @steipete/github --global --force` | Exit `0`; installs from ClawHub without risk/block output. Live skill JSON does not currently expose `channel`/`isOfficial`. |\n| NVIDIA skill install | `node dist/entry.js skills install @nvidia/tao-setup-nvidia-gpu-host --global --force` | Exit `0`; installs GitHub-backed ClawHub skill without risk/block output. Live skill JSON does not currently expose `channel`/`isOfficial`. |\n| Bundled skill surface | `node dist/entry.js skills info peekaboo --json` | Exit `0`; reports `source: \"openclaw-bundled\"`, `bundled: true`, no ClawHub trust warning. |\n\nCurrent ClawHub API caveat: sampled Peter/NVIDIA skill detail and install responses identify the owner but do not expose a structured official field. The client code and tests support official skill bypass as soon as ClawHub returns `channel: \"official\"` or `isOfficial: true` on skill detail, owner detail, install resolution, or archive metadata.\n\n### Automated Checks\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/cli/plugins-cli.install.test.ts src/plugins/clawhub.test.ts src/skills/lifecycle/clawhub.test.ts src/plugins/install-security-scan.runtime.test.ts src/plugins/install.npm-spec.test.ts src/plugins/install.test.ts` passed: 438 tests across 3 shards.\n- `git diff --check` passed.\n- `node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p tsconfig.core.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/core.tsbuildinfo` passed.\n- `node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p test/tsconfig/tsconfig.test.src.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/test-src.tsbuildinfo` passed.\n\n<details>\n<summary>Existing screenshot proof pack</summary>\n\n## Screenshots\n\nThese are rendered transcript excerpts from `node .artifacts/clawhub-install-trust/run-proof.cjs` at PR head `b08ced424daa970c466e2fd80aca944ba5f4ac54`. They are included because the changed CLI output is the human-visible behavior reviewers need to inspect.\n\n| Group | Screenshots | Claims proved |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| Plugin installs | 5 | Malicious blocks, suspicious acknowledgement gate, community clean install, official/source-linked clean install. |\n| Skill installs | 5 | Same trust gate for archive-backed skills, including owner-qualified labels and official/source-linked skill metadata. |\n| Plugin updates | 3 | Malicious latest release blocks download and recommends uninstall; suspicious updates require acknowledgement; installed plugin remains unchanged when blocked. |\n| Skill updates | 3 | Same malicious/suspicious update behavior for archive-backed skills. |\n\n### Plugin Installs\n\n#### Plugin malicious release blocked before download\n\n<img width=\"2352\" height=\"1044\" alt=\"plugin-malicious\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/201566a4-69cc-46d6-883d-230ec1bb20a8\" />\n\n#### Plugin suspicious release blocked without acknowledgement\n\n<img width=\"2352\" height=\"1004\" alt=\"plugin-suspicious-no-ack\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/b76e128a-cf90-49d6-bf64-045a8de12111\" />\n\n#### Plugin suspicious release succeeds with acknowledgement\n\n<img width=\"2352\" height=\"1203\" alt=\"plugin-suspicious-ack\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/45fee826-f19c-4d29-bcdb-45484ac0fa01\" />\n\n#### Plugin community clean install succeeds\n\n<img width=\"2352\" height=\"726\" alt=\"plugin-community-clean\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/d09e6c6a-8e58-45db-aff1-8a14e291ab38\" />\n\n#### Plugin official/source-linked clean install succeeds\n\n<img width=\"2352\" height=\"726\" alt=\"plugin-official-clean\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/77f2a7c5-4540-404a-99fb-5783714269d3\" />\n\n### Skill Installs\n\n#### Skill malicious release blocked before download\n\n<img width=\"2352\" height=\"765\" alt=\"skill-malicious\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/169cf9cd-b283-4d5c-acf3-3765082733b5\" />\n\n#### Skill suspicious release blocked without acknowledgement\n\n<img width=\"2352\" height=\"805\" alt=\"skill-suspicious-no-ack\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/1660778e-57f2-4206-8ce7-151ecde51705\" />\n\n#### Skill suspicious release succeeds with acknowledgement\n\n<img width=\"2352\" height=\"845\" alt=\"skill-suspicious-ack\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/e1f34608-45d3-4406-aed3-490d9c96ff20\" />\n\n#### Skill community clean install succeeds\n\n<img width=\"2352\" height=\"368\" alt=\"skill-community-clean\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/1ce7783f-a387-4a10-b8b6-fe9ccf6c0719\" />\n\n#### Skill official/source-linked clean install succeeds\n\n<img width=\"2352\" height=\"368\" alt=\"skill-official-clean\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/704c4360-4215-458a-a76c-327174e7e553\" />\n\n### Plugin Updates\n\n#### Plugin update blocks malicious latest release\n\n<img width=\"2352\" height=\"1163\" alt=\"plugin-update-malicious\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/5a7c053c-2f81-47e4-b3c6-fcea74ea5cfb\" />\n\n#### Plugin update blocks suspicious latest release without acknowledgement\n\n<img width=\"2352\" height=\"1004\" alt=\"plugin-update-suspicious-no-ack\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/1e7151cd-d6b9-4c89-aee5-ab9b5b022986\" />\n\n#### Plugin update allows suspicious latest release with acknowledgement\n\n<img width=\"2352\" height=\"1203\" alt=\"plugin-update-suspicious-ack\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/fb85ecd3-03b2-4812-98ae-8cfa076a29ff\" />\n\n### Skill Updates\n\n#### Skill update blocks malicious latest release\n\n<img width=\"2352\" height=\"805\" alt=\"skill-update-malicious\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/a568eab0-d7f0-423b-91cd-4630db3a9db3\" />\n\n#### Skill update blocks suspicious latest release without acknowledgement\n\n<img width=\"2352\" height=\"805\" alt=\"skill-update-suspicious-no-ack\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/a28bd2f9-8cb9-4c64-917c-e00fde777911\" />\n\n#### Skill update allows suspicious latest release with acknowledgement\n\n<img width=\"2352\" height=\"845\" alt=\"skill-update-suspicious-ack\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/eb2cd4e4-c112-4349-a8c2-597a024a9496\" />\n\n</details>\n\n## Known Gaps\n\n- Full `pnpm check`, full build, and Crabbox/Testbox were not rerun in this checkout.\n- Latest live official ClawHub plugin packages require newer OpenClaw compatibility than this stale PR base (`2026.6.8`). A branch refresh onto current `origin/main` (`2026.6.10`) should allow the same live official plugin installs to pass compatibility after the trust-bypass path.\n",
